      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is painful to feel like emotional numbness drains the meaning out of those \"chemical reactions,\" forcing existence into suffering rather than joy. Many find solace not in trying to conquer death, but in committing to selfless acts or deep connections that linger beyond the self for those hurt or impacted. If suffering feels unbearable or self-destructive, harming yourself to escape this pain is dangerous and hopeless.",
